(18, 'How to Prepare for IIT-JEE?', 'How-to-Prepare-for-IIT-JEE', '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Cracking the <strong>IIT-JEE</strong> exam, one has to make a well-structured study plan. It is essential for the students to be academically sound as well as he/she has to inculcate skills like analytical skills, time management, exam-taking strategy, and situational intelligence. Aspirants appearing in this exam should make headway and start preparing for the exam in a sincere manner. In this blog, you&rsquo;ll get to know about some important tips to <strong>crack JEE Advanced</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Tips and tricks to crack JEE Advanced Physics:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Learn every formula properly:</strong> As you study Physics, just write down all the formulas and remember them by heart.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Learn the Derivation Of The Formulas:</strong> Learning the derivation of the formulas helps in remembering and understanding them easily. The derivations of formulae are important for JEE Advanced because questions are asked on its alternatives.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Focus On important Topics:</strong> Once your fundamental and major concepts are cleared, concentrate on the scoring topics like Electrostatics, Rotational Motion, Wave Optics, Laws of Motion, Alternating Current, Ray Optics.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Tips and tricks to crack JEE Advanced Chemistry:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Form your strategy in a systematic manner:</strong> Start with clearing the most important concepts from Physical and Inorganic chemistry both. Dedicate a major portion of your time to Organic chemistry. Leave the qualitative analysis for the end as it requires memorizing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Be patient with Organic Chemistry:</strong> The things involved in Organic chemistry might seem difficult at first. Do not dive too deep for understanding the concepts as we are short on time. Start making notes to easily memorize syllabus at the end.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Practice Reactions:</strong> Practice the most scoring topics, equations, concepts, and related problems on a daily basis.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Tips and tricks to clear JEE Advanced Maths:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Conceptual Clarity is a must:</strong> Clear the fundamental concepts of all the chapters. Maths is all about formulas. In order to remember them properly, understand and practice different applications of the formulas on a daily basis.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Solve Practice/Sample Questions:</strong> Solving JEE Advanced level practice questions after completing every topic is very important.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Previous Year&rsquo;s Question Papers:</strong> Practicing from JEE advance previous years question papers is crucial when you are preparing for JEE Advanced Maths<br />\r\nAll of this ensures that you have a personalized study plan that includes your strengths and weaknesses and guides you accordingly until you achieve your aim.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Cracking the <strong>IIT-JEE</strong> exam, one has to make a well-structured study plan. It is essential for the students to be academically sound as well as he/she has to inculcate skills like analytical skills, time management, exam-taking strategy, and situational intelligence. Aspirants appearing in this exam should make headway and start preparing for the exam in a sincere manner. In this blog, you&rsquo;ll get to know about some important tips to <strong>crack JEE Advanced</strong>.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Tips and tricks to crack JEE Advanced Physics:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Learn every formula properly:</strong> As you study Physics, just write down all the formulas and remember them by heart.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Learn the Derivation Of The Formulas:</strong> Learning the derivation of the formulas helps in remembering and understanding them easily. The derivations of formulae are important for JEE Advanced because questions are asked on its alternatives.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Focus On important Topics:</strong> Once your fundamental and major concepts are cleared, concentrate on the scoring topics like Electrostatics, Rotational Motion, Wave Optics, Laws of Motion, Alternating Current, Ray Optics.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Tips and tricks to crack JEE Advanced Chemistry:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Form your strategy in a systematic manner:</strong> Start with clearing the most important concepts from Physical and Inorganic chemistry both. Dedicate a major portion of your time to Organic chemistry. Leave the qualitative analysis for the end as it requires memorizing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Be patient with Organic Chemistry:</strong> The things involved in Organic chemistry might seem difficult at first. Do not dive too deep for understanding the concepts as we are short on time. Start making notes to easily memorize syllabus at the end.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Practice Reactions:</strong> Practice the most scoring topics, equations, concepts, and related problems on a daily basis.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Tips and tricks to clear JEE Advanced Maths:</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Conceptual Clarity is a must:</strong> Clear the fundamental concepts of all the chapters. Maths is all about formulas. In order to remember them properly, understand and practice different applications of the formulas on a daily basis.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Solve Practice/Sample Questions:</strong> Solving JEE Advanced level practice questions after completing every topic is very important.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>&bull; Previous Year&rsquo;s Question Papers:</strong> Practicing from JEE advance previous years question papers is crucial when you are preparing for JEE Advanced Maths.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll of this ensures that you have a personalized study plan that includes your strengths and weaknesses and guides you accordingly until you achieve your aim.</span></span></span></p>\r\n', 'imgpsh_fullsize_anim5.png', 'Dr. IITian', '2020-01-20'),
(20, 'What is IIT-JEE?', 'What-is-IIT-JEE', '<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\">IIT stands for <strong>Indian Institutes of Technology</strong> was started in 1951. In its initial years (1951-1954), students were allowed on the basis of their academic results followed by an Interview in various centers across the country. It is an autonomous public academic institute with 23 campuses all over India. The IITs is a successful visionary venture of India&rsquo;s first Prime Minister, Nehru. The functioning of all the IITs is governed by the Institutes of Technology Act, 1961 where the Indian president is the most powerful dignitary within the management of IIT, serving as the ex-officio visitor. Another government dignitary, the Union HRD Minister is the ex-officio Chairperson of the IIT Council.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Ranked best when it comes to engineering colleges in India, the <a href=\"https://www.iitsystem.ac.in/\"><strong>Indian Institutes of Technology</strong></a> are a dream come true for science stream students. Students initiating of the IITs are known to possess acquired professional excellence in life. Either, getting admissions for further studies in most prestigious Universities abroad, or getting a job in any reputed company within the world, IITians are always given first priorities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Every year, the IITs conduct a Joint entrance exam (JEE) to pick candidates for the 4-year B.Tech, B.Pharm, 5-year B.Arch, Integrated M.Sc., and M.Tech courses, or getting employment in any reputed organizations within the world, IITians are always demanded.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In 2015, media publication house Outlook India&rsquo;s top engineering colleges had 7 IITs within the count. The <strong>23 IIT campuses in India</strong> are located within the following cities:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mumbai, Maharashtra</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dhanbad, Jharkhand</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mandi, Himachal Pradesh</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Roorkee, Uttarakhand</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Jammu, J &amp; K</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Delhi, Delhi</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kanpur, Uttar Pradesh</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Patna, Bihar</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Guwahati, Assam</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kharagpur, West Bengal</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bhuvaneshwar, Orissa</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hyderabad, Telangana</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dharwad, Karnataka</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Tirupati, Andhra Pradesh</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Madras, Tamil Nadu</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Panjim, Goa</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The present count of IIT alumnus has crossed the two lac bar among which here is listing the foremost popular ones you&#39;ll be able to recognize right now:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sundar Pichai (Chief executive officer at Alphabet)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>N. R. Narayana Murthy (co-founder and former chairman of Infosys)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sachin Bansal and Binny Bansal (Founders of Flipkart)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ajit Gupta71(founder, president, and CEO of Aryaka)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Vic Gundotra (former Senior vice chairman at Google)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Krishan Kant (former Vice-President of India)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Nandan Nilekani (Co-founder of Infosys, Chairman of the Unique Identification Authority of India)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Arvind Kejriwal, Chief Minister of Delhi</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Jairam Ramesh, Former Minister</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The IITs receive significant funding from foreign governments (USSR, USA, Germany) or world organizations like UNESCO. They also receive funding from the govt and also the private sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Upcoming Exam Dates for IIT-JEE:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>JEE Mains 2020</strong> January Session entrance test will be held from 6th to 9th January 2020. The April Session exam will be conducted from 3rd April till 9th April 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><strong>The Pattern of IIT JEE Exam:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Nowadays, the IIT JEE is a single-stage <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/blogdetail/How-to-Prepare-for-IIT-JEE\">objective type examination</a> consisting of two papers of three hours duration each to check comprehension &amp; analytical ability of candidates. Both Paper-1 and Paper-2 will each have three separate sections on Physics, Chemistry &amp; Mathematics. All questions are going to be of Objective Type, designed to check aptitude, comprehension and analytical ability of the candidates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Eligibility for IIT JEE:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates appearing in (10+2) or equivalent qualifying examination, must secure a minimum of 60%(55% for SC/ST and PD) marks in aggregate in their respective Board Examination.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>A student can have only two attempts to write down the JEE in the year during which he or she passes the XIIth standard examination and/or in the following year.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates who join any of the IITs, IT-BHU, Varanasi, and ISM, Dhanbad through JEE won&#39;t be permitted to seem for JEE in the future.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates should be less than 25 years in age, with five-year relaxation for SC, ST.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Candidates can attempt the exam at most two times in two consecutive years.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The selection process for IIT-JEE:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>One exam for admission to IITs, NITs, and IIITs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The new JEE will incorporate 2 Tests viz. Main Test and Advanced Test which will test problem-solving ability in basic science subjects - Physics, Chemistry, and Maths. Both Tests are going to be of 3 hours duration each.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Only the topmost 1,50,000 candidates, based on their performance in JEE (Mains) will qualify to appear within the JEE (Advanced) exam, which will rank the aspirants for admissions to IITs, provided the applicants are among the highest 20% high scorers of their respective boards at school XIIth examination.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; For FREE DEMO CLASSES&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/registration\">Enroll Now</a></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'What_is_IIT_JEE.jpg', 'Dr. IITian', '2020-01-21'),
(21, 'How To Find The Best IIT JEE Coaching Classes/Institute?', 'How-To-Find-The-Best-IIT-JEE-Coaching-ClassesInstitute', '<p><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\">When we target our goals, they work in two methods: We work on them and then they work on us! Same as our strategies and goals towards our career. Success cannot be achieved in one day, it requires a proper course of action, a systematic analysis of our approach to reach the goal, implementation of policies and plans and much more.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\">If you&rsquo;re an ordinary student of class 10th or 12th and you dream to become successful in life, you cannot achieve it in one day or even in one year. Extraordinary students or for instance, say toppers are toppers because they are always pre-planned for the next step of their career; they&rsquo;ve already decided in <strong>10th or 12th standard</strong> that at which position they will stand after 10-12 years.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\">If you&rsquo;re also <a href=\"https://bit.ly/39Rtrxc\"><strong>dreaming to start your career</strong></a> and become one of those extraordinary ones, you have a hell lot of career opportunities and a wide range of fields to enter in. One of these fields is IIT JEE, where you&rsquo;ll get utmost respect for being an IITian, a state of honour in society, an ample amount of knowledge and a stable job in the most reputed companies of the world with the highest amount of package as compared to others.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\">As you must be knowing the fact that, IIT-JEE isn&rsquo;t a walk in the park, or I could say nigh on impossible and this is quite demanding due to better growth options. The competition is also very high. But you need not worry if you wish to pursue IIT-JEE, then this blog is very useful for you. You&rsquo;ll get a complete idea regarding <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/blogdetail/How-to-Prepare-for-IIT-JEE\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">how to prepare for IIT JEE</a> and to choose the best coaching classes for IIT JEE.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\">Here are a few things which should be considered while choosing the <strong>best coaching institute</strong> for the preparation of IIT JEE:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong>Experienced and Proficient Teachers - </strong>Teachers play the most crucial role in the preparation of an IIT aspirant for the examination. Experienced teachers are considered to be most capable because they have their own techniques of teaching. Teachers should have the ability to motivate their students for better performance. The professionalism of the teacher regarding education and learning standards matters a lot for cracking this exam. It is also important for students and parents to communicate with teachers while visiting <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/about\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">coaching classes for IIT JEE</a> coaching.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong>Past Achievements - </strong>Past results are the most important basis to judge the competency of a coaching institute. Generally, coaching institutes advertise the percentage of scoring students, which does not give the correct picture about the institute&rsquo;s performance so the best way to analyze the score of last year&#39;s result is by communicating with previous year&rsquo;s students and parents who were the part of that coaching. You must do a complete background check of the coaching institute.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong>Study Material for IIT JEE - </strong>Pertinent study plays a major role in deciding the future of your career. Study material should be up to date and must be capable of clearing the concepts. The difficulty level and the language of the study material should match with level exams. So you should discuss and check the study material of the respective coaching institute in which you are planning to take admission.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong>The Infrastructure of the Class - </strong>Before joining any institute, you should ensure the Infrastructure, safety, and assurance of what coaching center&rsquo;s offer you on your joining day and in brochures/templates. Class strength is also an important factor in your learning because more strength means less attention of the teacher and it will lead to confusion in concepts. So you should ensure it before enrolling yourself in any coaching institute.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong>Types of Courses Taught</strong>: Although most of the coaching classes offer almost the same kind of courses, the important point is to check the duration of courses, timings of classes, availability of experienced teachers specifically for the Optional Subject of your choice, revision batches, and doubt sessions.</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong>Other Things You Must Consider Are:</strong>