(26, 'How To Prepare For School Final Exams', 'How-To-Prepare-For-School-Final-Exams', '<p><strong>Final Exams</strong> are the last obstacle for the students to the next class. These exams carry a lot of weight so every student must appear in the exam at the end of their academic year. No matter, how much have you studied during the year but in the few days before the examination, try to do your best and prepare yourself for the exams. Here are some helpful and useful ways about <strong>how to prepare for final exams</strong> in one month and get everything else done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Time Management:</strong> Manage the remaining time for preparations and revision of all the subjects. Keep a record of what you&rsquo;ve revised rather than repeating the same topics. Create a balanced study program so that you will be able to study all the subjects. Don&rsquo;t mix up all the subjects. Make a time table of all the tasks you have to do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Prepare Revision Notes:</strong> With the comprehensive syllabus of subjects, it becomes difficult to revise all the topics before the examinations. Prepare a notepad and point the notes for the important concepts which you can use to brush off for the Exam Preparation. Avoid mugging up at last time because it can result in forgetting everything you have learned. Instead, pick up your brief notes which you&rsquo;ve made while the subject was going on in the classroom or coaching. Reading the notes at the final preparation can help you remember all the main concepts and write good answers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Solve Previous Years Question Papers:</strong> One of the most fruitful ways to prepare for exams when you don&rsquo;t have much time is to solve the previous year&rsquo;s question papers. This ensures you to know the format of the question paper and get you to hang out the exam time limit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Never Cram Before the Exam:</strong> Almost all the students have a habit of learning and Cramming lessons and concepts before the start of the exam. This is totally wrong. It is advisable not to read new topics before the exam as you may forget the things you have already know. Learning before the exam is just like Cramming.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. Don&rsquo;t Panic!</strong> Don&rsquo;t let stress affect you. Don&rsquo;t nervous while <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/\">preparing for the exams</a>, it&rsquo;s just an exam. Yes, you have a huge syllabus to cover up and also there are a lot of expectations. But, do not let stress overwhelm your preparations. At the time of the exam, if a question seems too difficult, write the rest of the questions you know, and then return to the ones you left blank. Stay calm and tell yourself that you will do it all.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Write Neat, Present Well:</strong> Presenting your answer sheet in a proper way has more chances of getting good marks in the subjects. For this, practice more and more for writing better answers in exams so that you can score well. Use your time properly to get the maximum result out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7. Revise Within 24 Hours:</strong> Firstly, make sure that you don&rsquo;t touch uncovered syllabus or unlearned concepts a few days before your exams and if you do so, just remember the three R&rsquo;s which are very important- review, recap and reinforce. Any new topic you learn needs to be Reviewed, Recapped and Reinforced in the duration of 24 hours. Science tells that if you failed to do so, you failed to remember an 80% portion of the topic you&rsquo;ve learned. Revise it within a period of 24hours in order to let it endure in your mind for a long time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8. Shift Between Subjects:</strong> Before you get on to your studies, there are different types of subjects which can be categorized as Memory-subject, Problem-solving evaluation, Analysis- based subjects. For most efficient learning, you should rotate between each subject categories in a long period of study time. Don&rsquo;t do multi-tasking in studies. This is one of the best practices among how to study in less time. Study until you thoroughly understand a subject or a topic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>9. Get Enough Sleep:</strong> This step is very much important when it comes to studying hard as most of the students stay awake till night to finish revising before exams. But this is not the right way. Always remember that it is your proper sleep that transforms your short-term memory (what all you&rsquo;ve read/revised or learned till now) to long-term retaining memory (what you can remember while sitting in the exam hall).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>10. Take Care of Your Health:</strong> It becomes very important to maintain a healthy lifestyle even if you&rsquo;re left with ample time for your exams. Start with healthy breakfast, healthy lunch &amp; a light dinner as it will keep your mind alert and fresh all day long. Try to stay away from highly-processed food like sugary beverages, oily junk food. Remember, a good diet is vital for optimal study. So, say no to fast foods &amp; yes to home-made fresh food. Keeping a healthy &amp; nutritious diet always is a must for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>11. Shut Down Social Media:</strong> It may sound hard! But, yes a little reduction of social media can do wonders for you! After all, the social media platform isn&rsquo;t going anywhere right? So, keep the distraction to social media for some time, at least for a month till your exams end. &nbsp;Close down all your accounts on all social media for a while or don&rsquo;t use cell phones at the time of the study.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>12. Explain Your Answers to Others:</strong> You can try group studies to share learnings and encourage studying. Take the interest in studies by explaining your answers to friends. This will not only help you in remembering things better but also it can highlight any weak area in which you are lacking behind &amp; need more hard work.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These are some of the final exams study hints to help you score much better in exams. Hence, avoid pressure &amp; start acing every single minute. These 12 useful study tips for exams will surely crack your syllabus in the last few days &amp; will help you in scoring better this time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:16px\"><em>All the best for your exams!</em></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Exam_Preparations04.jpg', 'Dr. IITian', '2020-02-07'),
(27, 'Last-minute Tips for Board Exams 2020', 'Last-minute-Tips-for-Board-Exams-2020', '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The <strong>Central Board of Secondary Education</strong> (CBSE) on December 18, Tuesday, declared the CBSE Class 10th and Class 12th examination dates. The CBSE class 10th 2020 examination schedule and the CBSE 12th 2020 examination schedule was published by the exam conducting authority on the official website </span></span><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><a href=\"http://cbse.nic.in/newsite/\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"color:black\">http://cbse.nic.in</span></a></span></u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">The CBSE 10th and 12th examination for the year 2019-20 will commence from February 15. Students who are preparing for the board exams can download the date sheet from the official website.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You already know that to prepare a career milestone like class 12 or class 10 exam is not an easy task but not a difficult one too. With a decent study plan and essential materials, any student can score more in the CBSE Board examination.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">The board exam is very stressful in the career of a student. Better <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/blogdetail/How-To-Prepare-For-School-Final-Exams\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">preparation for board examination</a> can lower down the stress completely. We are providing some useful tips in the subsequent part of this article which will encourage you to get the best score in your 12th examination. Some students copy to other intelligent students in preparation which is wrong. Know your skills and do not waste your precious time to know about how others are preparing. Focus your mind to start your own preparation and do not lower your confidence.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How to prepare for 12th board exams?</span></span></span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">Board exams are important for your future career. This exam holds a crucial factor for streams, colleges and institutions. Students who are appearing in the 10th or 12th<sup> </sup>class examinations can surely take guidance from these tips and tricks:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Confidence: </span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Some of the bright students lack in their confidence. They have a better idea to study, good concentration and enthusiasm in their study but they always think negative about the result. They always take their studies as seriously as it becomes a load over them. Therefore, try to study with fun. Take your studies seriously but do not get this seriousness over your confidence. Always think positive about your exam. Positive attitude towards exams is the main fact which you should have in yourself to successfully crack the board exam.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Time Management:</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"> Time management is another important element in your preparation. You need to prepare a timetable for your study and give equal time to all subjects. If you follow this tip, you will surely be able to avoid the stress and fear which arise in the students during the preparation of the exams. Set a deadline for every subject, and then only you will able to complete your studies within time.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Revision: </span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">To complete the study in time is essential, but revision is more important in your study. Revision is just like a final touch to your studies. Don&rsquo;t wait till the end to revise and mug up. Pick your weekend day as the most suitable day for your regular revision about whatever you have studied during the whole week. Complete your all subjects around 15 days to 1 month prior to the final board examination, so that you can do the revision again.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Study Method:</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"> Set your study hours and the right place to study. Give more time to the subjects which are more difficult than that of others on which you already have a grip. It will make those subjects easier at the time of examinations.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Write Notes: </span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Writing is a good habit to learn efficiently. Always write the subject wise notes including definitions and concepts over the topics that you are studying. At the time of the exam, these notes will help you with your revision.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Refreshment and rest: </span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\">Give some time to the refreshment activities daily. Take a good 6-7 hours of comfortable sleep. Ensure that your bed is much convenient for sleep. Take regular exercise and jogging. Eat healthy food. These above-mentioned things will make you fit for the next day study and make your brain active and able to increase your output.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The time before the exams: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Students are strictly advised to not read any new topic just before the exams. Get up early in the morning and review the important topics you have marked. Stay comfortable and stress-free and be self-confident about your preparations for the examination.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Go with the syllabus: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Take details about the syllabus of all subjects thoroughly. Besides preparing from reference books, you should also prepare from your syllabus books like NCERT books. Syllabus books are created by keeping in mind the strict syllabus of the examination. Stick with the prescribed syllabus and read respectively.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Work on Weak points:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"> Have a look at what are your weak points and how can you make them solid. Examine your answer sheets of class tests and pre-board and take a deep look into them and find your errors. Make a list of your weak points for every subject and start doing hard work on your weak points and make them strong.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Break into achievable targets: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#242424\">You already know that the syllabus is vast, you cannot complete it at one time. Allow equal time and complete the syllabus in parts.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#242424\">Set an objective for yourself either daily or weekly and achieve it. Apart from your school studies, you can study a little extra if you have more time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Say no to distractions: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#242424\">While you are studying, you should cut yourself from the causes of distractions like smartphones, Social Media, and all. If it is adding meaning to your study like any academic-related video from YouTube, then you should watch. But ensure that you have set a particular time for that. If you stay away from distractions, it will easy for you to focus properly on the studies. You should stay focused as much as possible. So you can easily get discarded from the source of distractions.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#242424\">Solve sample papers and previous year&rsquo;s question papers:</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#242424\"> After completion of the syllabus, it is a good way to prepare and be ready for the exam. The more you prepare and solve question papers, the more positive you become. You will also get an idea about the type of questions coming in the exam. Previous year question papers will help you to know the relevant and repetitive topics from any subject. By solving previous year papers, you will have a rough idea about the changes in question type in various subjects during a specific period of time.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#242424\">So get ready, be prepared: All the Very Best</span><strong><span style=\"color:#242424\"> - Dr. IITian</span></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Board_Exams_10th_12th.jpg', 'Dr. IITian', '2020-02-10'),
(28, 'How to Crack and Score High in JEE - Expert Guidance Tips', 'How-to-Crack-and-Score-High-in-JEE-Expert-Guidance-Tips', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">JEE</span></strong><span style=\"color:black\"> is one of the most popular entrance exams for undergraduate in India. Students who want to take entry in engineering colleges give JEE exam. To clear the JEE exam it&rsquo;s necessary to prepare excellently. Here we provide you with some <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/blogdetail/Tips-to-Avoid-Negative-Marking-in-IIT-JEE-NEET\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">Tips to clear JEE exam</a> and how you can score high in the exam. Here are the guidance tips in the form of question answers to make you understand more clearly and make this blog interesting for readers.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">1.&nbsp; Why should we understand the concepts instead of learning them?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">The JEE exams are near about to be conducted. Theory and questions based directly on the syllabus are decreasing. If you understand the concept, then it will really help. Since JEE tests your combined understanding of multiple problems through a single question.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">2. Why is it important to concentrate on class 11 syllabus?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Both CBSE and JEE syllabus have questions from your class 11 syllabus. Moreover, chapters in class 11 form the basis of your class 12 exam. If you don&rsquo;t understand completely your class 11 syllabus, you will not be able to grasp a lot of what is explained in class 12. This is very helpful with Maths. Understanding topics like Calculus, Conic Section, and Trigonometry taught in the 11th help with other lessons in class 12.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><em><span style=\"color:black\">In this blog, we&rsquo;ve now moved on to discussing each subject, topics that he found difficult, and the ones that he found easy.</span></em></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">3. How important are theorems when it comes to physics?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">They have certain conditions and if you don&rsquo;t apply them correctly, you will not be able to solve physics problems correctly. I think that when it comes to physics, practice is the core key. You should be capable to read the question, understand the situation and conclude from which chapter the question is from. This will help you understand which set of formulae you will require to solve it promptly and accurately.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">4. What&rsquo;s the distinction in the testing pattern for theorems, when it comes to CBSE and JEE?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">In JEE, understanding how the theorem is derived is sufficient. Questions are majorly around the applicability of that theorem. However, CBSE questions you on how well you remember every step of the derivation. They need you to recreate the same steps from NCERT books or else you will lose your marks. So when you are preparing for CBSE, concentrate on NCERT steps, language, and examples. When asked which topic is considered the toughest in <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/courses/best-iit-jee-coaching-in-indore\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">JEE Main</a>, We&rsquo;ll say that questions based on Rotation were both tough and interesting.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">Moving on to Chemistry</span></em></strong></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">5. How to study organic chemistry?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">When it comes to organic chemistry it is crucial to understand the concepts. That&rsquo;s because JEE does not hold on to the same examples. You need to read the question and then apply these concepts to be able to find out the reaction. So you should totally be focused on concepts.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">6. How to tackle numerical in chemistry?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Most of the numerical are a part of physical chemistry. There are very fewer formulae and theorems, but the applications are very different. This is why mastering in numerals will only come through a great practice of as many sums as you can.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><em><span style=\"color:black\">Next, we will discuss how to practice concepts.</span></em></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">7. When should we start taking mock tests?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You should start taking mock tests from the very beginning. Once you complete a particular section, you should go through mock tests to solve questions from that chapter. As you move ahead with the practice, the number of chapters that you attempt in each mock test kept increasing.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">8. When did you start practicing the previous year&rsquo;s question papers?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You should attempt a few in the early days of your preparation, but usually, everyone practices towards the end. JEE candidates should not attempt these sample papers in the hope that questions might be the same, but only to learn time and stress management.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">9. How to improve your weak areas?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You should keep an &ldquo;Error Book&rdquo;. After every test &mdash; be it a practice test or a mock test, you should make a note of questions that you did wrong, along with the correct answer. Over time, you must focus on doing that type of questions accurately. This will ensure you to strengthen your weak areas.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:black\">10. How to study chapters that need memorising formulas, reactions, or diagrams?</span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\"><a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/courses/best-jee-main-advanced-coaching-indore\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">JEE</a></span></strong><span style=\"color:black\"> has a very less percentage of the portion that examines your memory skills. To tackle that, you should make flashcards. You must write down all the formulae and reactions and read them every day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">At the end of months, once your concepts are clear, concentrate on giving mock tests, and keep your &ldquo;Error book&rdquo; updated. Give the exam in different orders of the three subjects to find out which order suits you properly. Also, keep your flashcards safe. The JEE portion has over 100 topics, it is impossible to learn them all last minute.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">While giving the exam, do the easy questions first. Those are areas where you can score high marks without any trouble. Also, attempting these questions will calm you down and give you more assurance to attempt the tough ones.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Aside from all of this, always be motivated and keep working hard. Even if you aren&rsquo;t perfect with numerical from the beginning, keep practicing them and you will improve over time. <strong><a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">Dr. IITian</a></strong>, Indore wishes all the aspirants and the students for their upcoming examinations.</span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>For Experts Guidance</strong> <strong><a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/registration\">ENROLL NOW...</a></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Crack_Score_High_in_JEE_01.jpg', 'Dr. IITian', '2020-02-18'),
(29, 'Tips to succeed in IIT-JEE & NEET Exams', 'Tips-to-succeed-in-IIT-JEE-NEET-Exams', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">Here you&rsquo;ll get the <strong>Exam Preparation Tips</strong> along with the methodologies to crack competitive exams like IIT-JEE and NEET.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">1. Know The Details Of The Exam: </span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">This is the first thing you have to do before you jump into the exam preparations like for jobs and colleges. Know the details about the exam, the selection process, the level of knowledge expected, because you can shape your pathways, only when you know your goals.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">The basic rule is to know about the exam and the college you want to apply for. Do your research about the exam and college requirements as well as the level of knowledge and expertise required to crack the exam. Get an extensive knowledge of the exam curriculum. If possible, talk to people who have previous experience on the subject on social networks, conferences, blogs, etc.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">2. Prepare Your Strategy: </span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">After the basic know-how, prepare a strategy to fulfill your goals. Most of the exams have two steps in the selection process. One the written exam and the other is college counseling. So, you have to plan your preparation respectively.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">Instead of offering some vague suggestions, I will answer it to the point. For written exams, make a strategy to finish the syllabus much before time. Once you complete your syllabus, you are in a position to revise your concepts as many times as you want (if time permits). Along with that, you can practice for practical or mathematical questions multiple times, once you go through the whole syllabus. Remember, practices and revisions add up your confidence which will lead to your success.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">3. Arrange Study Materials: </span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">When you know, what you have to study, you are almost done. Next, you have to arrange the study materials needed to crack the written examination. Every department has their own set of study material suggestions. In some cases, one single book even helps in two or more exams.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are preparing for <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/courses/best-iit-jee-coaching-in-indore\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">IIT-JEE</a> and <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/courses/best-neet-coaching-institute-indore\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">NEET</a> exams, then find the common topics/subjects between the exam syllabuses. See, for the books that can be used for both purposes. This will lessen your workload as well as the time for preparation. And most importantly this will save your money too. Buy those books that have a good reputation and are highly recommended among the candidates who are giving the same exam. Meeting with experienced guys who have already succeeded may be of great help in this regard.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">4. Make Routine:</span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"> A Routine is very crucial. Without any reliable routine, your studies may sound directionless. When you have a couple of papers, it would not be simple to study all the papers with the same importance, if you haven&rsquo;t scheduled them properly. Remember that your routine should be a feasible one and not something that only a superman can do. Try to follow the routine rigorously over a long period of time. Hope that would bring you nearer to your accomplish your aims.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">While making a routine you have to keep a few things in your mind. The allocation of time should be based on your knowledge and learning ability. Subject proficiency should be the driven part in preparing your routine. Also, review the routine from time to time and change it as per your progress. Try to keep practical or mathematical subjects for practice every day in your routine as they required great exercise to score in the exam.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">5. Prepare Yourself By Writing What You Have Learned: </span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">The students mostly have a drawback for writing habits. The Associate Professor Anne Mangen at the University of Stavanger&rsquo;s, in research, said, writing by hand strengthens the knowledge process. Reading your own handwriting in a subject, dramatically improves your grip on the subject.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have to go back to your school days. You may find things very silly, but it&rsquo;s a fact. You have to write everything you learn. You don&rsquo;t need to write lengthy answers, but brief or point-wise answers will work. Save your writing notebooks for the future when you need quick revisions for the whole subject particularly during exam days.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">6. Solve Previous Years&rsquo; Question Paper:</span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"> If you are preparing for exams, solving previous years&rsquo; question papers surely helps you. All you can have an idea about the question patterns, their mark allocations, etc. Moreover, there&rsquo;s a strong perception that by solving previous years&rsquo; question papers, makes it easier for a candidate to find out the common questions.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">The mock test is an <a href=\"https://www.driitian.com/blogdetail/How-to-Crack-and-Score-High-in-JEE-Expert-Guidance-Tips\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">effective way to prepare for exams</a>. Create an atmosphere affecting the examination hall and complete previous years&rsquo; question papers within time. By practicing it for a number of times before you sit for an examination you can excel in your time management abilities. As it is seen in most of the cases, students/candidates fail just because they couldn&rsquo;t answer all the questions during the specified time period.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">7. Improve Your Vocabulary:</span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"> Since most of the exams are conducted in English or have a subject paper on the English language, you should be perfect in the language. English grammar is also an important topic to be covered by the student. Though you shouldn&rsquo;t be an expert, yet a Standard English is demanded from you. Another important thing is to use appropriate idioms and proverbs in sentences to improve your writing manifold.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">The best way to improve your linguistic skills is to read English publications and magazines. Watching English news can improve your oratory skills. Moreover, English movies with sub-titles are great to understand as well as show your feelings in that language. Whenever you come up with a new word consult dictionary and see their application in sentences. Consult official books on idioms and proverbs and learn their usage. You can also have online dictionaries or mobile applications for your ease.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">8. Keep Yourself Motivating:</span></span></strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\"> Motivation is the key-driven force to success. Well, it&rsquo;s not always possible to crack these exams in the first instance. You should have patience. Keep yourself motivated until you get the expected result.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">How Will You Do That?</span></span></em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">Meditation is an age-old way to improve your concentration level. That brings a state of self-belief which improves the confidence level in you. To crack&nbsp;IIT-JEE or NEET, exams you need a high amount of determination and an encouraging approach.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">Conclusion</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">It is true that sometimes our preparation and work don&rsquo;t match our performances in the exams. But that doesn&rsquo;t demean our struggles. If we stick to our level of competence to try for the desired result, we will not be denied success.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">These exams require a deeper conceptual clarity on the topics. Mere speculations and half-hearted efforts in the exams will not take you the path of success. Precise hard work and tireless effort are the only keys to success. Follow the above tips and try to inculcate a good learning habit, the results would be bright.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Tip_for_IIT_JEE_NEET_02.jpg', 'Dr. IITian', '2020-03-02');
